<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-50] The Lustre Ops Manual should doc LNET/LND options for peer_timeout and avoid_asym_router_failure</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-50</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Peer health detection and asymmetric router failure detection avoidance options are not documented in the Lustre Ops Manual.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bugzilla 24404 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=24404&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=24404&lt;/a&gt;) provides some guidance for these options and also calls out some other undocumented LNET/LND option that need improvement.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13787">LUDOC-50</key>
            <summary>The Lustre Ops Manual should doc LNET/LND options for peer_timeout and avoid_asym_router_failure</summary>
